text: Marietta Sangai Sirleaf (born April 12, 1970), professionally known as Retta, is an American stand-up comedian and actress. She is best known for her roles as Donna Meagle on the NBC sitcom Parks and Recreation and Ruby Hill on NBC's comedy-drama Good Girls. ==Other websites== * * Category:1970 births Category:Living people Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:Actors from New Jersey
